About the Company
Our Client is a global leader in supply chain management solutions.
Responsibilities
We're looking for an engaging and driven HR Manager to be responsible for partnering with various internal business stakeholders to identify and design solutions for training & development of employees.
Implement and facilitate employee onboarding, orientation and transition programmes;
Analyse training needs and develop training matrices for organization & department goals;
Schedule training activities by coordinating with relevant training providers;
Coordinate training assignments, both local and overseas, for employees;
Evaluate and report on training effectiveness;
Ensure that online training systems are up-to-date;
Develop trainee and intern programmes;
Research and identify best practices for training & development;
Drive continuous improvement and develop organizational policies and practices for training.
Requirements
Degree in Business, Human Resource Management or other related fields;
At least 4 to 5 years of relevant experience;
Experience in designing and implementing organisational development initiatives in a multinational corporation;
Stakeholder management skills;
Effective communication skills, with the ability to facilitate discussion and influence decision makers;
Good command of English, and comfortable writing training-related articles;
Strong drive towards continuous improvement.
Employment Details
Work location: East Singapore;
Attractive remuneration and benefits;
Supportive work environment
Get in touch with us
